==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mellite
<hw>Mel"lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mel</ets>,
<ets>mellis</ets>, honey: cf. F. <ets>mellite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a honey color, found in brown coal,
and partly the result of vegetable decomposition; honeystone. It is a
mellitate of alumina.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mellitic</ent>⟦br⟧
